text:
the #metoo movement, which was sparked last fall after the new york times and the new yorker brought to light harvey weinsteinâ€™s long history of sexual harassment and assault. shortly thereafter, women across the world shared their own experiences â€” demonstrating, in the process, just how many have kept quiet for years about discrimination, abuse, and rape. powerful men in media and politics have been forced to resign as a result, after allegations surfaced about their behavior.

but rather than encouraging employees to speak up about harassment, or implementing better training programs, many wall street executives have had a different reaction to the #metoo movement. according to a report this week from @bloomberg, male executives areâ—ï¸avoiding one-on-one dinners with women and refusing to sit next to them on flights, out of fear of being falsely accused of doing or saying something inappropriate â—ï¸ this type of backlash, of course, threatens to do real harm to the careers of women in banking, where success depends in large part on networking and going out to dinner â€” oftentimes with just men. â€œwomen are grasping for ideas on how to deal with it because itâ€™s affecting our careers,â€ karen elinski, the president of the financial womenâ€™s association.â €
â €
"instead of going out of their way to avoid being alone with female colleagues, male executives can simply try behaving themselves", an unnamed investment adviser told bloomberg. his advice to executives who worry that their actions might be misinterpreted: â€œjust donâ€™t be an asshole.â€ word.â €
________â €

text:
over the weekend hlokomela & 225 of hoedspruitâ€™s farm workers march in solidarity with the â€œ16 days of activism against women and children abuseâ€. this march forms part of our annual â€œ#aids dayâ€ celebrations, & this year the event was hosted at rederberg estate.  the 3km walk started at the snake park road & ended at the rederberg soccer field towards moriah. the eventâ€™s aim was to raise awareness on hiv & aids, remember the loved ones weâ€™ve lost to the disease, & to sensitise community members about gender based violence.

as part of the dayâ€™s activities , two local female soccer clubs participated in a friendly soccer match, with the winning team walking away with a full new soccer kit. (including kit, flags and soccer nets.) other activities included a dialogue on the theme â€œshatter the silence. stop the violence. #metooâ€, a talk by guest speaker, captain thete,  from the saps on gender based violence, & a candle light memorial to remember & honour those who have passed over the last 13 years.

a big thank you to our partners for delivering the services that made this day possible. thank you to the caterers, entertainment team & the nompilos for making this such a fun day. 
a big thank you in particular to the rederberg estates, saps hoedspruit, maruleng traffic department, department of social development & @discovery_sa for their massive support.

text:
be careful who you bury. 
itâ€™s all fun and games until well intentioned people unearth them,

shake the barrow dirt from their clothes,

and link hands,

bracing them behind the back of the newly emerged,

placing their bewildered feet on the pathway of life.

be careful who you bury. 
you may discover the prepossessing puppet who bowed to your depraved structure was something else entirely. 
you buried steel beneath that delicate headstone.

darling, this is not your grave.

text:
on human rights day, the world marks 70 years since the adoption of the udhr. the declaration was born out of wwii to ensure that all human beings are born free and equal with dignity and rights (article 1). sadly, weâ€™re not there yet. today, 50% of refugees uprooted from their homes from conflict, persecution or natural disasters are women and girls. and their specific needs and voices are often neglected. 
thankfully, insightful roadmaps are provided. a report, turning promises into action: gender equality in the 2030 agenda for sustainable development, exposes the major gaps in current data about what works for women and girls, particularly those who are most marginalised. so whatâ€™s the key takeaway? gender equality, womenâ€™s human rights and the intersectional approach woven into the sdgs are critical for achieving every one of the 17 goals. letâ€™s take it from there!

for more, click the link in our bio.

text:
all hail the king of kings!!! in humble adoration, i return to give you praise. .

believe when i say, god is good, god is real and he is always in a good mood!!! .

i am eternally grateful for the gift of salvation and all that comes with it.
.

lord i return all the glory to you.
.
.

there is nothing i did this year or will still do that was by my strength or doing. it was/is simply by the grace of god.
.
.

i did not qualify but his call qualified me. so if you sometimes feel like you don't qualify, guess what? #metoo. but you need to move beyond that and believe you are worth his investment/calling.
.
.

if he calls you, then he qualifies you. settle it in your mind. galatians 2:20 will help us all... if he can use me, trust me, he can use you. the question is, "are you avaliable".
.
.

this year is indeed my year of covenant realities.
.

i also want to thank you for being part of my 2018.
.
.

i am grateful and i return to thank him
.
.

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this picture was taken tonight at 6:47pm, a picture of me smiling..... with teeth showing! i must have been feeling great. i never smile with my teeth..... i felt beautiful, gorgeous, understood, and respected. at 6:55 i hung up a call with a close friend to go through the tsa security line at san diego international airport. @tsa this is when you brought me down. took my self worth. took it all, molested me, violated me. you basically threw it in the trash. i was essentially detained for being transgender..... at san diego international airport my groin was flagged on the body scan. and i refused to be searched and have my groin patted down by a @tsa officer, who refused to call me a woman, the entire time. i was misgendered and treated more poorly than i ever have been since going through transition.  i was told i have two options. allow them to rescan me and program the machine to scan me as a man, or be arrested if i was patted down in the groin area and anything was felt between my legs. 
itâ€™s interesting how your subordinates supported me, told me that they didnâ€™t understand why this was happening. told me that they were sorry that this was happening. grabbing handfuls of paper towels for me to dry my tears and wick away the snot that was dripping down my face as i cried and shook uncontrollably with terror. 
i took my only option to make it home. i took away everything iâ€™ve worked for and stood up for when i cowardly gave up my fight and allowed you to scan me as a male, only to have my chest flagged on the body scanner. only to be molested on my chest. simply to end the tirade. so i could go home. i gave myself up to you. 
i didnâ€™t survive 7+ years of childhood sexual trauma to go through this as an adult. i didnâ€™t stand up to the last man who violated me to be molested by a â€œpublic servantâ€.
i will stand up. and i will fight. because no man, woman, or child ever deserves to be treated the way i was at sdia, or anywhere else in america. what lies between my legs is my business.
#metoo 
i am so depressed i canâ€™t stop crying. i was told that because of the way i present myself, that this was my fault. this isnâ€™t how i present myself. this is me.

text:
#triggerwarning #mynewnormal #mynewreality 
last week i fell prey to an individual that allowed his demons to take control of him and work their evil on me.  i was shopping, i had put my items in the back of my car and then went to out my cart away as i always do...my car doors still unlocked.  30 seconds, that is all it took, and he managed to sneak into the backseat of my car without me seeing him.  please, please, please be careful, be vigilant, be aware...and always always lock your doors even if just returning your cart to the cart return.

my attacker has since been found...but he took his own life in the process.  it is an odd hallow feeling...but i am thankful he can no longer hurt anyone else.  and, he will not destroy me nor my spirit...i refuse to give him that power after all he tried to take from me.  i survived, i am alive, and i will rise!
.
.
.
.
#becareful #stayvigilant #stayaware #survivor #iamasurvivor #rapesurvivor #metoo
name: Raye Sweezea
tweet_full:
#triggerwarning #mynewnormal #mynewreality 
last week i fell prey to an individual that allowed his demons to take control of him and work their evil on me.  i was shopping, i had put my items in the back of my car and then went to out my cart away as i always do...my car doors still unlocked.  30 seconds, that is all it took, and he managed to sneak into the backseat of my car without me seeing him.  please, please, please be careful, be vigilant, be aware...and always always lock your doors even if just returning your cart to the cart return.

my attacker has since been found...but he took his own life in the process.  it is an odd hallow feeling...but i am thankful he can no longer hurt anyone else.  and, he will not destroy me nor my spirit...i refuse to give him that power after all he tried to take from me.  i survived, i am alive, and i will rise!
.
.
.
.
#becareful #stayvigilant #stayaware #survivor #iamasurvivor #rapesurvivor #metoo

today also marks the 70th anniversary of #humanrightsday. good day to pledge as citizens to make our #cities and public spaces #safer and more accessible to half of our population - the #women. link to the full film in our bio. .
.
.
.
.

text:
i realize that i'm never going to fit in anyone's box. like lots of little black girls, i was taught that my personality, excitement and curiosity was a nuisance and i needed to go sit down and stop being "fast". this rejection taught me to very powerful lessons. 1) i had to work hard as fuck to be loved and if it didn't work, it was my fault. 2) i would never be good enough to be loved just for being me. i donâ€™t even need to tell you the type of pain that incision in my life from learning these lessons.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
it has taken and continues to take work at accepting all this glorious, juicy, brilliant divineness. but this is the healing work. regardless of what anyone else did to me, it's my responsibility to heal the broken places because that little girl is still deserving of love and acceptance.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
she deserves to be seen and i'll be gotdam if i'm going to stand in the way of her getting her shine!â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

text:
banyak sekali kasus kekerasan yg terjadi, apalagi terhadap perempuan.
kekerasan itu sendiri merupakan suatu tindakan agresi dan pelanggaran yang dimaksudkan untuk menyebabkan penderitaan atau menyakiti orang lain.
.
.
kekerasan bisa terjadi dalam bentuk verbal (ucapan) maupun non verbal (tindakan).
.
.
1,5 juta siswa sma diseluruh negara mengalami kekerasan fisik oleh pacarnya dan masih banyak lagi kasus kekerasan yang terjadi terhadap perempuan
so, berhenti melakukan kekerasan terhadap perempuan.
.
.
.

text:
my desk is brimming with activity, tasks that need completed, and moments to sip early grey tea. i awoke to a start this morning with great positive thoughts for this monday and week. my feelings have not changed god gave me another day on this earth to give of myself to others. as i sit and reflect this morning, my mind wanders from the holiday activities planned, to finish decorating for christmas, to baking with my teens and husband, to wait when did i go back to the abused child of my past and tears. the television is on id channel and they are talking of a little girl who was sexually abused. i am there again crying for myself and that little girl that no one helped. i am mad at myself for going down the rabbit hole this morning.  my mind wanders over the lifetime of abuse i suffered until i said, "no more!" then, i find my strength and pull from within, it will not win, i am going to love, show this world compassion, center myself in peace, and focus on my angel that hangs over my desk. a gift from an artist friend and i center in light...

text:
the me too movement (or #metoo movement), with many local and international alternative names, is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault  #metoo spread virally in october 2017 as a hashtag on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplaceit followed soon after the sexual abuse allegations against harvey weinstein. tarana burke, an american social activist and community organizer, began using the phrase "me too" as early as 2006, and the phrase was later popularized by american actress alyssa milano, on twitter in 2017. milano encouraged victims of sexual harassment to tweet about it and "give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem"â €
â €
